  <title>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Resilience through Arts for SA Farming Communities</narrative>
  </title>
  <description>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">* The families in farming communities in the Western Cape of South Africa remains a marginalized group that suffers the psycho-social effects of apartheid and ongoing trauma. * This project use the arts therapies to develop resilience in individuals and their communities, towards a sustainable solution to alcohol and substance abuse, gangsterism, violence and abuse. * We will run arts-based projects with children, their parents, unemployed youth, teachers and other community leaders.</narrative>
  </description>
